This is a known breaking change. Google deprecated `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` in API 30, and .NET 10 enforces **edge-to-edge** rendering on Android, which makes that API a no-op.

## What to do instead

**1. Use `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` (enabled by default)**

MAUI's built-in auto-scroll should handle focusing the `Entry`/`Editor`. If you previously disabled it, re-enable it:

```xml
<!-- On your page or control -->
<Entry
    android:KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Enabled="True"
    xmlns:android="clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Platform;assembly=Microsoft.Maui" />
```

**2. For a chat-style pinned input bar, react to IME insets**

The auto-scroller focuses individual controls but won't push a bottom-docked bar up. Use Android's `WindowInsets.Ime` in a platform-specific handler:

```csharp
// In Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs (or a helper)
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Controls.Compatibility.Platform.Android;

public static void ListenForKeyboard(Android.App.Activity activity, View rootView)
{
    ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(rootView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
}

class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View view, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

        // Bottom padding = max of keyboard or nav bar
        int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);
        view.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottom);

        return insets;
    }
}
```

Wire it up in `OnCreate` after `base.OnCreate`:

```csharp
protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

    var rootView = Window!.DecorView.FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;
    ListenForKeyboard(this, rootView);
}
```

**3. Keep your XAML layout simple**

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*,Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}" ... />
    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1" Padding="8">
        <Entry Placeholder="Type a message..." HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
        <Button Text="Send" />
    </HorizontalStackLayout>
</Grid>
```

The insets listener applies bottom padding to the root Android view, pushing your entire MAUI layout (including the pinned input bar) above the keyboard. No MAUI-level `SoftInputMode` calls needed.

**TL;DR:** Replace `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` with an `OnApplyWindowInsetsListener` that reads `Ime()` insets and sets bottom padding on the root view.
